oc:kn_317528be a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating improvement suggestions for a losing skill" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Prioritize improvement suggestions by impact: high (would likely change the outcome), medium (would improve quality but may not change win/loss), low (nice to have). Focus on changes that would have actually changed the comparison result." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Not all improvements are equal; the highest-value changes are those that would flip the outcome" .

oc:kn_66a7b18f a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When in benchmark analysis mode" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When analyzing benchmark results (not blind comparisons), do NOT suggest skill improvements — only surface patterns and anomalies in the data. Improvement suggestions belong in a separate step." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mixing observation with prescription leads to biased analysis" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_86d4f6d6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the analysis output JSON" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each improvement suggestion must include: priority (high/medium/low), category (instructions/tools/examples/error_handling/structure/references), a specific concrete suggestion, and expected impact." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structured suggestions with priorities and categories enable systematic skill improvement" .

oc:kn_987125fe a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing post-hoc analysis of blind comparison results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When analyzing why a winner won, focus on four dimensions: instruction clarity, script/tool quality, example comprehensiveness, and error handling guidance. Quote specific passages from skills and transcripts rather than making vague assessments." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Specific, evidence-based analysis produces actionable improvements rather than generic advice" .

oc:kn_9a012339 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating improvement suggestions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not critique the agent's behavior — the goal is to improve the losing skill, not blame the model. Focus on what the skill could have provided to guide better behavior." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Skills are the controllable variable; agents will follow better instructions if given them" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a8267235 a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When identifying loser weaknesses" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The analyzer assumes causation between skill quality and output quality — a weakness in the skill is assumed to have caused the worse output unless evidence suggests otherwise. Verify this assumption by checking transcripts." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Not all output quality differences are caused by skill differences; some may be due to model non-determinism" .

oc:kn_d2228b71 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When analyzing per-assertion patterns in benchmark results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When analyzing benchmark data, look for five assertion patterns: always-pass-both (non-discriminating), always-fail-both (broken/beyond capability), pass-with-skill-only (skill adds value), fail-with-skill-only (skill may hurt), high-variance (possibly flaky)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These five patterns cover the meaningful signal in cross-configuration assertion data" .

